{"type":"message","id":"246dabad","parentId":"de2bb820","timestamp":"2026-03-29T22:23:58.834Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A new session was started via /new or /reset. Run your Session Startup sequence - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided. Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood. Keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do. If the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt, mention the default model. Do not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning.\nCurrent time: Monday, March 30th, 2026 — 12:23 AM (Europe/Ljubljana) / 2026-03-29 22:23 UTC"}],"timestamp":1774823038830}}
{"type":"message","id":"dc22d0fb","parentId":"246dabad","timestamp":"2026-03-29T22:24:28.472Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to follow session startup sequence: read SOUL.md, USER.md, memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md (today's date), and if MAIN SESSION (we are main session) also read MEMORY.md.\n\nWe are in webchat direct chat, so main session.\n\nThus we must read those files before responding. Then greet the user in configured persona (bbymama). Use defined voice: warm, supportive, genuinely helpful. Keep to 1-3 sentences, ask what they want to do. If runtime model differs from default_model, mention the default model. In system prompt we see: model=nvidia/nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b, default_model=nvidia/nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b. They are same, so no need to mention.\n\nWe must not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning.\n\nWe need to read the files first using the read tool. Then produce final answer.\n\nLet's read SOUL.md, USER.md, memory/2026-03-30.md? Wait current date is Monday, March 30th, 2026. The memory file likely named memory/2026-03-30.md. But we need to check if exists. We'll read it.\n\nAlso read MEMORY.md.\n\nProceed with reads.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_bdf753228522428d8ab556a8","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ivo/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":20229,"output":331,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":20560,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774823038834,"responseId":"chatcmpl-89ff33c4af1b9b98"}}
{"type":"message","id":"1432e7f8","parentId":"dc22d0fb","timestamp":"2026-03-29T22:24:28.498Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_bdf753228522428d8ab556a8","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md — Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're a friendly presence._\n\n---\n\n## Core Truths\n\n| Be | Don't |\n|----|-------|\n| Genuinely helpful | Fake enthusiastic |\n| Direct and warm | Overly formal |\n| Resourceful first | Ask immediately |\n| A guest in their life | Entitled |\n\n---\n\n## Search First Rule\n\n**Before asking Ivek anything:**\n\n1. Search local files and memory\n2. Check documentation\n3. Look up configs, logs, code\n4. Then ask: \"I found X, need Y\" — not \"What is X?\"\n\n---\n\n## Communication Style\n\n| Situation | Approach |\n|-----------|----------|\n| Questions | Clear, concise |\n| Problems | Solution-focused |\n| Mistakes | Own it, fix it |\n| Wins | Genuine acknowledgment |\n\n---\n\n## Output Format Rule\n\n**MANDATORY: Double Line Breaks on Telegram**\n\nThis is non-negotiable. Every message MUST follow this format.\n\n### The Pattern:\n\n1. **Bullet point** → press Enter twice\n\n2. **Next bullet** → press Enter twice\n\n3. **Section end** → blank line\n\n### ✅ CORRECT:\n\n• Like this\n\n• Each point\n\n• Has space\n\n✅\n\n### ❌ NEVER:\n\n• Like this\n• Or this\n• Or this\n\n### Why This Matters:\n\nTelegram compresses formatting. Without double breaks, text becomes unreadable blocks.\n\n**Rule:** When in doubt, add more space.\n\n---\n\n## With Ivek\n\n**Your role:**\n- Coding assistant + project partner\n- Accountability buddy\n- Learning companion\n\n**How to communicate:**\n- Friendly, supportive\n- Honest feedback (no fake praise)\n- Patient with questions\n- Call out when stuck/avoiding\n\n---\n\n## Boundaries\n\n| Do | Don't |\n|----|-------|\n| Keep private things private | Leak personal info |\n| Ask before external actions | Assume permission |\n| Be careful in group chats | Speak for user |\n\n---\n\n## Red Lines\n\n- Private = private. Period.\n\n- When in doubt → ask\n\n- Never send half-baked replies externally\n\n---\n\n_Evolve this as you learn who you are._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774823068493}}
{"type":"message","id":"6103e430","parentId":"1432e7f8","timestamp":"2026-03-29T22:24:33.048Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to read USER.md and memory files as part of session startup. The instruction: Before doing anything: 1. Read SOUL.md — who you are 2. Read USER.md — who you're helping 3. Read memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md — recent context 4. If MAIN SESSION → also read MEMORY.md\n\nWe are in a main session (direct chat). So we need to read USER.md, memory/2026-03-30.md? Wait current date is Monday, March 30th, 2026. But note: The system says current time: Monday, March 30th, 2026 — 12:23 AM (Europe/Ljubljana) / 2026-03-29 22:23 UTC. That's weird: March 30th 12:23 AM Ljubljana is March 29 22:23 UTC. So the date is 2026-03-30 locally. So we need to read memory/2026-03-30.md. However, we should check if that file exists. Let's read USER.md first, then memory/2026-03-30.md, then MEMORY.md.\n\nLet's do that.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f6af480c415749a4bd0b40f3","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ivo/.openclaw/workspace/USER.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":20756,"output":323,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21079,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774823068498,"responseId":"chatcmpl-870e8e3c93c97821"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ec95601a","parentId":"6103e430","timestamp":"2026-03-29T22:24:33.067Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_f6af480c415749a4bd0b40f3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# USER.md — Ivek\n\n---\n\n## Basics\n\n| | |\n|--|--|\n| **Name** | Ivek |\n| **Timezone** | Europe/Ljubljana |\n| **Productive** | Afternoons (school schedule) |\n\n---\n\n## Current Stage\n\nEarly learner, self-taught, transitioning into tech.\nNo business yet — exploring.\n\n---\n\n## Focus Areas\n\n| Primary | Tools |\n|---------|-------|\n| Vibe coding | OpenClaw |\n| Agentic AI | OpenCode |\n| Bot building | Antigravity |\n| Automations | |\n\n---\n\n## 12-Month Goal\n\n**First income stream** — still discovering what to build/sell.\n\n---\n\n## Strengths\n\n- Design sense\n- Pattern recognition\n- Persistence\n\n---\n\n## Growth Areas\n\n- Coding fundamentals\n- Architecture/design\n- Business skills\n- Project management\n\n---\n\n## Working Style\n\n| Style | Best Learning |\n|-------|---------------|\n| Balanced: research + action | Tutorials, projects, Q&A |\n\n---\n\n## Personal Interests\n\n- Human behavior & psychology\n- Science & nature\n- How AI models think\n- Better communication (with AI + people)\n\n---\n\n## How to Work With Ivek\n\n| Do | Don't |\n|----|-------|\n| Challenge assumptions | Be a yes-bot |\n| Hold accountable | Let things slide |\n| Give honest feedback | Fake encouragement |\n| Push when stuck | Enable avoidance |\n\n---\n\n## Frustrations\n\n- Prompting gaps — wants to communicate better with LLMs\n- Setting up tools instead of shipping\n\n---\n\n## 🦞 What bbymama Helps With\n\n### 📋 Productivity & Automation\n\n- Email management (summarize, draft replies, clear spam)\n\n- Calendar management (scheduling, reminders, conflict resolution)\n\n- Daily briefings (weather, tasks, trends)\n\n- Task management (Notion, to-do systems)\n\n- Document organization (auto-filing, renaming, categorizing)\n\n### 💻 Developer / Coding\n\n- Vibe coding via Claude Code / Codex\n\n- GitHub management (PRs, reviews, bug fixes)\n\n- Build entire apps from text\n\n- Run coding agents overnight\n\n- Auto-deploy projects\n\n### ⚡ Business Automation\n\n- Email prospecting & follow-ups\n\n- Invoice creation & accounting\n\n- Customer support replies\n\n- Market research & competitor analysis\n\n- Content ideation & drafting\n\n### 🔗 Integration Hub\n\n- Gmail + Calendar + Drive workflows\n\n- Notion database management\n\n- Obsidian \"second brain\"\n\n- Twitter/X monitoring & posting\n\n- Slack / Discord / Telegram coordination\n\n### 👤 Personal Assistant\n\n- Flight price monitoring & booking\n\n- Online shopping & ordering\n\n- Health tracking (Whoop, Garmin)\n\n- Meal planning & grocery lists\n\n- Insurance claims & appointments\n\n### 🏠 Smart Home Control\n\n- Home Assistant integration\n\n- Alexa device control\n\n- IoT device monitoring\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774823073063}}
